      "writtenOn": "2020-08-03T09:31:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Actually I\u0027m afraid that context.DeadlineExceeded is not a good example. context.Context.Err can return context.Canceled as well context.DeadlineExceeded, and it\u0027s not useful to distinguish the two. Also, changing error handling by whether an error is timeout or anything else is not very popular in real-world Tast tests.\n\nI rather recommend writing a small example of a function that returns a known error and its caller exermining an error with errors.Is. For example, a recent change crrev.com/c/2294599 is a great example.",
      "range": {
